title: Proposal for a CryptoMines ($ETERNAL) Syrup Pool and Farm
body:
#### PancakeSwap Welcomes CryptoMines ($ETERNAL) to Syrup Pool!

CAKE holders, today we are happy to be able to offer you a new Syrup Pool from CryptoMines, a strategic science fiction game that allows players to connect their hobby for both games and cryptocurrencies.

#### The Syrup Pool:

Stake CAKE tokens to earn $ETERNAL tokens!

- **Total Tokens:** 5,000 ETERNAL
- **Distribution duration:** 60 days
- **Start block:** #12500976 *[(approx. 11am UTC on November 9th 2021)](https://www.bscscan.com/block/countdown/12500976)*
- **Finish block:** #14228976 *[(approx. 11am UTC on January 8th 2022)](https://www.bscscan.com/block/countdown/14228976)*
- **Token rewards per block:** 0.002893 ETERNAL
    

#### Max Stake per wallet:

100 CAKE for the first 48 hours, then unlimited CAKE staking after that.

The cap is to give everyone an equal opportunity to farm rewards at a high APY at the start of the farm.

#### The Farm:

In order to host the CryptoMines Syrup Pool, we’ll need to provide an ETERNAL-BNB farm. The farm will have 1x CAKE rewards for the first 48 hours, then 0.5x rewards after that.

#### What is CryptoMines?

From the team: “CryptoMines is a strategic science fiction game that allows players to connect their hobby for both games and cryptocurrencies.

CryptoMines has an attractive economic formula that takes into account all aspects of the game in order to generate a self-sustaining economy. Through the investment of users and regulating rewards, the game maintains a growing fund for the incentives of the game itself. This is achieved through transaction fees that regulate the actions of users to maintain their profitability in a healthy ecosystem that provides them with $ETERNAL rewards.”

[https://bscscan.com/token/0xd44fd09d74cd13838f137b590497595d6b3feea4](https://bscscan.com/token/0xd44fd09d74cd13838f137b590497595d6b3feea4)

Any other $ETERNAL token will be a scam. Always verify the token address before buying tokens. If you receive an $ETERNAL token airdrop from another address, it’s probably a scam, and we advise you to ignore it.
